    "en": {
      "title": "A three-member committee to probe Nimal's bribery allegations",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A three-member committee has been appointed by President Ranil Wickramasinghe to investigate the allegation that former Minister Nimal Siripala de Silva received a bribe from a Japanese company during his tenure as the Minister of Ports, Shipping and Aviation.",
        "Retired High Court Judge Ms. Kusala Sarojani Weerawardena is the chairperson of the committee and the other members are retired Senior DIG SM Wickramasinghe and SMG Perera, a senior officer in the Administrative Service.",
        "The report of the committee should be submitted to the President before the 31st.",
        "Mr. Nimal Siripala de Silva resigned from the ministry recently, giving the opportunity for an investigation after the accusation."
      ],
